name: chlorohydroquinone
Reason: 1,2-propanediol, 3-(2-methoxyphenoxy)-, 1-carbam has a melting point of 92 degrees Celsius. The basic unit of analysis is the 1,2-propanediol moiety, which on its own exhibits intermolecular hydrogen bonding, thus increasing the melting point. The methoxy group introduces additional molecular weight and van der Waals forces, raising the melting point. The phenoxy group introduces additional pi-stacking interactions, further raising the melting point. The carbamate group introduces additional hydrogen bonding, further lowering the melting point. The chlorine atom introduces a significant dipole, increasing intermolecular forces and melting point. The hydrogen bonding is more significant than the dipole-dipole interactions, but the chlorine introduces more significant intermolecular forces.
